.SH NAME
Document.pointerlockchange_event \- Document: pointerlockchange event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]pointerlockchange\f[B]\f[R] event is fired when the
pointer is locked/unlocked.
.PP
The event handler can use \f[CR]Document.pointerLockElement\f[R] to
determine whether the pointer is locked, and if so, to which element it
is locked.
.PP
This event is not cancelable and does not bubble.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqpointerlockchange\(dq, (event) => { })

onpointerlockchange = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
Using \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R]:
.IP
.EX
